  "title": "ARCHITECTURAL DESIGNER CUM CO-ORDINATOR",
  "description": "<p><strong>Company Overview / Employee Value Proposition</strong></p><p>CSCE PTE. LTD.</p><p><strong>Job Summary</strong></p><p>Prepare and deliver architectural drawings and submission documents that comply with government standards and client requirements, supporting project approvals and coordination across multiple agencies.</p><p><strong>Responsibilities</strong></p><ul><li>Develop architectural drawings that comply with government standards and regulatory requirements to ensure project approval readiness</li><li>Incorporate and resolve client design queries to align architectural plans with client expectations and project specifications</li><li>Prepare detailed plans, documents, and forms for submission through the CoreNet system to facilitate regulatory review processes</li><li>Create and customize drawings for submission to agencies including JTC, HDB, URA, SCDF, NEA, PUB, LTA, NParks, and BCA, ensuring compliance with each agency’s specific requirements</li><li>Compile and prepare final submission packages for Temporary Occupation Permit (TOP) and Certificate of Statutory Completion (CSC) to support project completion approvals</li><li>Participate actively in project coordination, technical, and contractor meetings to communicate design progress, resolve issues, and align multidisciplinary teams toward project milestones</li></ul>",
